        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40341",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Closing as non-issue.\r\n\r\nUser can give language as locale in this case. Zend_Currency must have a full qualified locale or a country to know the currency to use. The language itself is not enough.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-02T07:47:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-02T07:47:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40342",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}User can give language as locale in this case.{quote}\r\nMeaning what? Zend_Currency($locale) throws the same error. As you can see I have set region (country) for Zend_Locale. ($locale is instance of Zend_Locale)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-02T08:22:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-02T08:22:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40343",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "When a user accesses your application and his browser sends \"en\" as locale, then you initiate Zend_Currency with \"en\".\r\n\r\nAs I can see you did NOT set a region for Zend_Locale. You just set a default locale, which means that this locale is used when your user does not send a locale.\r\n\r\nIn the case your user sends \"en\" as mentioned before the default locale IS NOT USED.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-02T08:52:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-02T08:52:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40344",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}When a user accesses your application and his browser sends \"en\" as locale, then you initiate Zend_Currency with \"en\".{quote}\r\n\r\nOuh, of course. I just forgot this after I had tried to use this Zend_Currency($locale->getDefault())... ok, maybe I have to parse that key from the array of default locale and use that as input.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
